Object.keys(userdata).map((element,index) => { // var end = Moment( element.data.rows.course.createdAt.substring(0,10)); // another date console.log("index",userdata[element].rows) let va = userdata[element].rows Object.keys(va).map(i=>{ console.log("i is: ",va[i]) }) // var duration = Moment.duration(now.diff(end)); // var days = duration.asDays(); // if(parseInt(days) <30){ // totalbalances += Number(element.rows[index].income.substring(1)) // } }); let totalcourse = userdata.count // let totalbalance = userdata.filter(dated- userdata.rows.createdAt.substring(0,9)< 30) if(redirect){ return } return (loading ==false)?
